let go of it. It's plainly very present here in the club and the
kind of music we book here and the people that hang out here, and
the cars kind of go along with it.
</P>
<P>
   ``On a scale of one to 10, I'd say my obsession is probably an
11,'' he continued. ``It's definitely my biggest passion, and it's
the reason I work so hard at the club, so I can do the car deal.''
</P>
<P>
   Greater love hath no man than these three for their cars. The
obsession begins in boyhood, when most car fanatics start designing
their dream cars on paper. From there, they progress to models, to
slot cars, to magazines devoted to the hot-rod world. Getting their
own rod is the ultimate emancipation from parental control, the
