it, Howard is the Michelangelo of the retro roadster: ``You look at
Gary and the way he thinks and the way he works with a car, he's as
much an artist as any sculptor in the world. He has the temperament
of an artist, and the taste and the skill and the eye, and the
obsession to make the car perfect.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of it is just being creative,'' said Vaughan. ``You take
a car and you change it, make it more pleasing, smoother, lower.
The fun part is driving down the street, preferably with a couple
of other guys driving 'em too. You're looking out the window and
