</P>
<P>
   She looked over and said, ``Nice car.'' He said, ``Thank you.''
</P>
<P>
   She said, ``Does it go fast?'' He said, ``Pretty fast.''
</P>
<P>
   When the light turned green, she floored it, leaving Young in
the dust, laughing in her rear-view mirror.
</P>
<P>
   ``She smoked me!'' said Young, still incredulous days later.
``In a Buick! Seventy years old, and she still remembered how it
was.''
</P>
<P>
   Don McLeese writes for the Austin American-Statesman, Austin,
Texas.
