<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Contributions have paid to buy thousands of
Sudanese from slavery in the past four years. One can only honor
the impulse and the effort. But is that the right thing to do? How
can it not be? Mustn't a life be redeemed from misery if it can be?
Yes, but ... (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for Cox
Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. _ It is just past 9
p.m., and from all corners of Disney's Central Florida empire,
processions of automobile headlamps can be seen pushing on, much as
in the concluding scene in ``Field of Dreams.'' Most of the huge
entertainment park has closed for the night and dozens of thousands
of people, spent in ways more than one, are returning home, or to
their nearby hotels. Disney built and they came., (Howard Kleinberg
is a columnist for Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Life is all backwards. If my
mother were still around, I'd probably be bugging her for a new
body and she'd still be giving me the same old answer. ``Wait until
you're older.'' MOVED.
</P>
