<P>
   HOTRODS-MUSIC _ What is it with music lovers and their cars?
Three car-crazy Austinites, guitarist Jimmie Vaughan, Continental
Club owner Steve Wertheimer and Chuy's owner Mike Young, spend lots
their money and time on old cars newly redesigned that look sharp,
just like in the good ol' 50s. During SXSW these cars and others
were seen; even Rhino Records will release a 4-disc ``Hot Rods &AMP;
Custom Classics: Cruisin Songs and Highway Hits'', a set inspired
by and dedicated to the three Austinites who celebrate the
inspiration of the open road on rock 'n' roll, from ``Maybelline''
through ``Little Red Corvette.'' (McLeese, Austin
American-Statesman). 50. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
