   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   SCIFI-NONSENSE _ ATLANTA _ Scientists take aim at aliens, UFOs
and even creationism in a session dubbed ``nonsense and science
fiction,'' at the American Physical Society's annual meeting. Also:
the Woodruff Arts Center opens a new exhibit: ``Microscapes: The
Hidden Art of Technology'' and a look at what's next for lasers in
medicine. (Seabrook, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   PHYSICISTS-HAWKING _ ATLANTA _ An interview with Stephen
Hawking, hailed as a modern-day Einstein, about his recent book and
his planned presentation March 23 at the American Physical
Society's annual meeting, in Atlanta. Michael Skube/Glennon/Tate
(tentative), with photos
</P>
