plans to move Tuesday, March 23, on the New York Times wire.
Questions? Please call Holly Ocasio Rizzo at 415-777-8811. &HT;     
   
San Francisco _  SECRETS-Ahi  _ Spicy, vibrant and delicious food
is what you'll find at AsiaSF, and the ahi burger is one example.
In this weekly column describing what makes a Bay Area restaurant's
dish a success, we'll tell how to make it. &HT;    With recipe, chef's secrets for success. 
 By Michael Bauer  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
San Francisco _  &UR; TASTE-Pita  &LR; _ This week, The Chronicle's panel of
professional tasters rates pita bread. &QL; 
 &UR; By Robin Davis &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
Napa Valley, Calif. _  &UR; KITCHEN-Helm  &LR; _ It's fitting there is a baby
rocking in a cradle in Maria Helm's kitchen. It's equally fitting
that little Emma Louise Sinskey's cradle is mechanized. The mixture
of traditiona and innovation characterizes the kitchen and home of
the executive chef of PlumpJack cafes/Balboa Cafe and her husband,
winery owner Robert Sinskey, in the Carneros district of Napa
Valley.
<P>
   With tip sidebar, recipes. &QL; 
 &UR; By Karola Saekel &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
San Francisco _  &UR; VIETNAM  &LR; _ A reminder of the connection between
Vietnam and France, the crusty banh mi sandwich has nourished a
nation for decades. No wonder it traveled to North America. &QL; 
 &UR; By Kim Severson &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
San Francisco _  &UR; BUGS  &LR; _ David George Gordon, author of ``The
