upon the pecking chickens, choose the one that met his or her
standards and have it butchered out back. Today, markets that
butcher on site are as scarce as hens' teeth, but one shop in
Berkeley, Magnani Poultry, is an offshoot of what was typical in
the early part of this century. &QL; 
