   PA-HDTV-TOWER (Philadelphia) _ The fight over an HDTV tower in
Philadelphia. By Michael Janofsky. With photo.
</P>
<P>
   KEVORKIAN-TRIAL (Pontiac, Mich.) _ Dr. Jack Kevorkian is
expected to cross-examine prosecution witnesses as his trial
continues. By Pam Belluck.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCIENCE (Will move in `a' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SOLVENTS-PREGNANCY (Undated) _ A new study links exposure to
solvents to birth defects and other problems among pregnant women,
but experts contend the research is seriously flawed. By Gina
Kolata.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-MANAGED-CARE (Undated) _ Participation in managed care
programs seriously curtails the time doctors devote to medical
research and charity work, according to new research. By Sheryl Gay
Stolberg. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BUSINESS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   EUROPE-MERGERS (Paris) _ For all the talk about Europe's single
market and single currency, very few cross-border deals have taken
place, and those that are in active discussions have run into
problems. Instead, there is a rapid trend toward consolidation
within national markets and a continuing desire to keep foreigners
_ particularly other European foreigners _ out. By Edmund L.
Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   OIL-MEET (Vienna, Austria) _ The Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries ratified a plan for its members to cut output
by 1.7 million barrels a day. By Youssef M. Ibrahim. With photo.
</P>
<P>
   DAIMLER-CHRYSLER (Detroit) _ Recent developments at
DaimlerChrysler. By Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   STEEL-IMPORTS (Washington) _ In the wake of the House vote to
limit steel imports, the Senate Finance Committee held hearings on
a Senate version of the bill. By Leslie Wayne.
</P>
