procedure that involves an ``internal brassiere'' formed of mesh.
It's one of the hottest techniques in the plastic-surgery business,
where breast reshaping, reduction and reconstruction take center
stage. (Includes a 4-column color photograph of a doctor inserting
a mesh into a woman's breast and a 2-column color photo of an
operating room)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: BREAST LIST: A list of options for reshaping the breast.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: SLEEP DISORDERS: There may be more to that wheezing,
snorting, rattling rat-tat-tat deep-within-the-throat snoring that
awakens you, your loved ones (and possibly even the neighbors) each
night. A sleep evaluation could reveal the condition of sleep
apnea. (Includes a 2-column color photo of a man, hooked up to a
mask-like device, undergoing a sleep apnea test)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: HEALTH NOTES: A quarter of the nation's nursing homes have
severe health and safety infractions that often go unpunished,
although the conditions jeopardize residents, federal auditors said
in a recent study.
