   NATO-KOSOVO (Washington) _ U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke fails to
convince Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic to accept a peace
deal in the troubled Serbian province of Kosovo and heads to
Brussels to brief NATO chiefs. Meanwhile, President Clinton
consults congressional leaders to curry support for a NATO
bombardment. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   SENATE-KOSOVO (Washington) _ With the NATO bombardment of
Serbian positions almost certain, the Senate scrambles to express
support for U.S. military personnel _ despite big questions about
wisdom of President Clinton's policies in the Balkan region. By
GREG McDONALD.
</P>
