<P>
   ETHIOPIAN-RUNNER-TRIAL (Addis Ababa, Ethiopia) _ Degaga (Mamo)
Wolde in 1968 became the second Ethiopian, after Abebe Bikila, to
win an Olympic gold medal. He also became a national hero and a
vital link in the rich tradition of distance running that has
distinguished Ethiopian athletes. Now he is on trial on charges of
genocide and illegal detention of prisoners during the reign of
terror that followed the overthrow of Emperor Haile Selaisse in
1974. Wolde, now either 67 or 68 years old, remains in the prison
he entered in 1993, protesting his innocence and waiting for a
deliverance he believes will come. By Jere Van Dyke.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-DUKE-NCAA (Undated) _ The Duke men's and women's basketball
teams are both in the Final Four in their respective basketball
tournaments. No school has ever won the men's and women's NCCA
titles in the same season, but Duke has a chance. By Ira Berkow.
</P>
<P>
   BKW-PURDUE (Undated) _ A look at the Purdue women's team, ranked
No. 1 in the nation and now headed to the Final Four with hopes of
winning their first national title. By Zack Burgess.
