   WASHINGTON/POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-US _ WASHINGTON - Developments at home as Kosovo standoff
appears headed toward hostilities. (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   w/ KOSOVO-CONGRESS _ WASHINGTON _ Senate leaders dropped plans
Tuesday to vote on a resolution denying funding for U.S.
participation in air strikes against Yugoslavia, and instead moved
toward passing a resolution supporting the troops. Sen. Kay Bailey
Hutchison, R-Texas, announced the decision after a White House
meeting with President Clinton. (Malone, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-STAKE _ Beyond humanitarian concerns, fear that fighting
in Yugoslovia could spill over into other countries _ including
Greece and Turkey _ is a driving force behind possible intervention
in Kosovo. President Clinton laid out this and other rationales for
intervention in a Tuesday speech. (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This story was on the budget for Tuesday papers and is
being updated and will move again for Wednesday papers.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RUSSIA _ MOSCOW _ With air strikes in Yugoslavia
apparently imminent, Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov on Tuesday
abruptly canceled his planned visit to the United States. (Holmes,
Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   CAMP2000-COLUMN _ Campaign 2000 column: Georgia Gov. Roy Barnes
is considering moving up the state's presidential primary to avoid
competing with the behemoths of the campaign season _ California
and New York. Georgians are busily lining up with presidential
campaigns, hoping an early association with a candidate will pay
off down the road. With their numbers so close in the House,
Democrats and Republicans who are considering running for the U.S.
Senate are meeting with resistance from unlikely sources. (Sherman,
Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-FRAUD _ WASHINGTON _ A Senate subcommittee holds second
day of hearings on Internet stock fraud. Witnesses include federal
and state securities regulators. (Glass, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
