<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ A broad sell-off sent stock prices sharply
lower Tuesday as worries about high valuations and forthcoming
corporate earnings led investors to pare their equity positions.
Chances that the United States might soon be involved in air
strikes over Kosovo only added to the anxiety. By Kenneth N.
Gilpin.
</P>
