</P>
<P>
   CISCO-MARKETPLACE (San Jose, Calif.) _ There are new and old
worlds in the communications equipment business, and they are
locked in a struggle to control the networks of the future. No part
of that battle is more intense than the fight to control how
standard telephone calls will be transmitted using the technology
known variously as Internet telephony or voice-over Internet
protocol, the language of cyberspace. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
