<P>
   KOSOVO-MILITARY-ASSESS (Brussels, Belgium) _ The Yugoslav armed
forces and paramilitary police units that NATO warplanes would
attack to try to stop the fighting in Kosovo are regarded as tough
and well-equipped, and far more powerful than the Bosnian Serb
forces that allied warplanes bombed four years ago. Before allied
warplanes would attack any of these forces, allied officers said,
NATO commanders would try first to destroy as much as possible of
Serbia's considerable ability to shoot down planes with its
sophisticated integrated air defense system. By Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   With map locating both NATO and Yugoslav troops and military
installations.
