<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Wednesday, March 24, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Mary Downes on the national-foreign desk at (206)
448-8158.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MERCY (Undated) _ The head of operations for a
Northwest-based aid agency in strife-torn Kosovo is refusing to
abandon his Albanian staff despite fears of imminent NATO air
strikes and massive Serbian retaliation. A phone interview with
Terry Heselius, a 66-year-old great-grandfather who has worked in
Kosovo for Mercy Corps International since 1993.
