<P>
   NTSB-CRASH (Springfield, Va.) _ Two horrifying plane crashes and
a disturbingly close call were caused by a rudder on the Boeing 737
that suddenly turned the plane in the wrong direction, federal
investigators argued yesterday. The investigators dispassionately
dismantled suggestions by Boeing that the two crashes and the third
incident could be blamed on pilot error and bad weather, instead
focusing on the rare phenomenon called ``rudder reversal.''
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.
