<P>
   VALDEZ-ANNIIVERSARY (Cordova, Alaska) _ The day was clear and
visibility on Prince William Sound was unlimited, but two escort
vessels hovered close by the Chevron Mississippi earlier this month
as the tanker swung past Bligh Reef. It was here, 10 years ago
today, that the unescorted Exxon Valdez, which had moved out of
shipping lanes to avoid icebergs calved by the Columbia Glacier,
ran aground and disgorged more than 11 million gallons of oil into
one of America's premier sanctuaries of nature.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   POLICE-CHAIRS (Seattle) _ Police work has always had its
inherent dangers, but the Seattle Police Department's
Identification Unit has apparently become a particularly perilous
place. In the last month, two employees slipped off their rolling
desk chairs and landed on the linoleum floor. In response, all the
unit's civilian employees have been ordered to undergo a training
session on how to safely sit in a chair.
</P>
<P>
   By Vanessa Ho. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-DEBUTS (Undated) _ Reviews of ``It's like, you know ...'' and
``The Norm Show,'' debuting Wednesday night on ABC.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
