   (NYT17) ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia -- March 23, 1999 -- ETHIOPIAN
RUNNER-2, 3-23 -- Aberash Wolde, wife of Mamo Wolde, the 1968
Olympic champion, sits in front of her husband's trophies during an
interview in their house. Wolde, who won the gold medal for wining
the marathon at the 1968 Olympic games, now is on trial on charges
of genocide and illegal detention of prisoners during the reign of
terror that followed the overthrow of Emperor Haile Selaisse in
1974. (Jere Van Dyk/New York Times Photo)
</P>
