patron negotiates the stairs at Celadon, a restaurant which also
provides a safe, secure elevator for its customers. Just a few
years ago, upstairs rooms at restaurants were used only for
banquets and the occasional over flow crowd. But the restaurant
boom, along with rising rents for street-level space, has led a
growing number of restaurateurs to expand upward. (Norman Y.
Lono/New York Times Photo)
