<HEADLINE>
FROM PINES TO PANDAS, SOUTHERNMOST CALIFORNIA OFFERS PLENTY TO SEE
</HEADLINE>
 
(Accompanies BC-LEGOLAND and BC-LEGOLAND-ATTRACTIONS) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TIM MADIGAN 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Beginning with Saturday's opening, Legoland California shoulders
its way in among southernmost California's top tourist attractions.
It was already a crowded field.
</P>
<P>
   _ Torrey Pine State Preserve ranks among the Pacific Coast's
most spectacular destinations. The visitor center at the top of a
mountain offers views of sandstone cliffs and the ocean hundreds of
feet below. On a clear day, Dana Point is visible, miles up the
coast in Orange County.
</P>
<P>
   The park is named for the rarest pine in the United States. More
than 6,000 of them grow on 17 acres. Eight hiking trails offer
tours through the trees and spectacular vistas of wildflowers.
</P>
<P>
   _ Shi Shi and Bai Yun, a pair of giant pandas, have taken up
residence at the San Diego Zoo, among the country's finest, even
before the bears arrived. Shamu remains the star at SeaWorld. At
the San Diego Wild Animal Park, a monorail tram takes visitors on a
50-minute safari into land where 3,500 animals roam freely in
native habitats.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cabrillo National Monument offers the best views of San Diego,
tours of the historic lighthouse, and hiking down to tide pools
below. In winter, the monument is also a prime vantage point for
whale watching.
</P>
<P>
   _ Several charter yacht companies offer more intimate glimpses
of the gray whales as they migrate from Alaskan seas to the
warm-water breeding lagoons of Baja California. The migration
season lasts from mid-December to mid-March, peaking in January.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call the San Diego Convention and Visitors
Bureau at (619) 232-3101.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Some prices for our trip:
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Air fare: $307 per person
</P>
<P>
   Rental car: $51 a day
</P>
<P>
   Hotel: $139 a night for a room with two double beds at the
Holiday Inn, Carlsbad, less than five minutes from Legoland
California.
</P>
<P>
   At Legoland:
</P>
<P>
   _ $32 for an adult ticket, $25 for kids 3-16. Seniors also pay
$25.
</P>
<P>
   _ $12 per T-shirt
</P>
<P>
   _ 75 cents for a souvenir pencil
</P>
<P>
   _ $16.25 for three burgers, three fries and three colas
</P>
<P>
   _ $12.25 for one order each of Swedish stir-fry and fresh
ravioli
</P>
<P>
   _ $5.75 for an order of beef and broccoli stir-fry
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
